---
import '../styles/index.css';
import Layout from '../../../shared/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Hyperspace Demo" package="@astroscope/hyperspace">
  <p class="text-lg mb-6">
    Pre-compressed in-memory static file serving for Astro. Save space, serve from hyperspace.
  </p>

  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title">Features</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
        <li><code class="badge badge-ghost">brotli + gzip</code> - Pre-compresses all static assets at build time</li>
        <li><code class="badge badge-ghost">in-memory</code> - Loads everything into memory at startup — no disk I/O per request</li>
        <li><code class="badge badge-ghost">immutable</code> - <code>/_astro/</code> files get <code>Cache-Control: public, immutable, max-age=31536000</code></li>
        <li><code class="badge badge-ghost">Accept-Encoding</code> - Negotiates best encoding per request (br &gt; gzip &gt; raw)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mt-6">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title">Usage</h2>
      <pre class="bg-base-300 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code>{`// astro.config.ts
import hyperspace from '@astroscope/hyperspace';

export default defineConfig({
  output: 'server',
  integrations: [hyperspace()],
});`}</code></pre>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm opacity-70">
        That's it. Build your project and all static files in <code class="badge badge-ghost badge-sm">dist/client/</code> are compressed and served from memory.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mt-6">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title">How it works</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Build</strong> — walks <code class="badge badge-ghost badge-sm">dist/client/</code>, compresses each text file with brotli (max quality) and gzip (level 9)</li>
        <li><strong>Startup</strong> — middleware loads all files + compressed variants into a <code class="badge badge-ghost badge-sm">Map&lt;string, CachedFile&gt;</code></li>
        <li><strong>Request</strong> — checks the map, negotiates encoding, returns from memory with correct headers</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
